on. The Nash embedding theorem is used in the\nsecond step, explaining the need to take $m$ relatively large.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Feb 2016 19:49:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Feb 2016 16:33:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 13 May 2016 18:35:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-25"}
